extAlign="Justify">The purpose of this enactment is to exclude all reading material from the application of the Goods and Services Tax.</Para></Block></Bill_Part><Bill_Part Part_Type="MainText" CountLines="Yes" RunningHead_E="Excise Tax Act"><Block Align="Yes"><Para Style="MainText_DocNo">2304</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes"><Para Style="Session_Reign">1st Session, 36th Parliament,</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes"><Para Style="Session_Reign">46 Elizabeth II, 1997</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes"><Para Style="MainBillOrigin">senate of canada</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes"><Para Bold="Yes" Style="MAIN@BillNo_Title">BILL S-10</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes"><Para Style="MAIN@ti;04">An Act to amend the Excise Tax Act</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><MarginalNote>R.S., c. E-15; <keep>R.S.,</keep> c. 15 (1st Supp.), cc. 1, 7, 42 (2nd Supp.), cc. 18, 28, 41, 42 (3rd Supp.), cc. 12, 47 (4th Supp.); 1988, c. 65; 1989, c. 22; 1990, c. 45; 1991, c. 42; 1992, cc. 1, 27, 28, 29; 1993, cc. 25, 27, 28, 38; 1994, cc. 9, 13, 21, 29, 41; 1995, cc. 5, 36, 41, 46; 1996, cc. 10, 20, 21, 23, 31; 1997, cc. 10, 26<br/></MarginalNote><Para LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Hyphenate="ON" TextAlign="Justify">Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate and House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><MarginalNote>1992, c. 28, s. 41(1)<br/></MarginalNote><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes"><B>1.</B> Schedule VI of the <I>Excise Tax Act</I> is amended by adding thereto the following Part:</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes" KeepWith="Next"><!--Heading:PART XI--><Para TopMargin="10" Hyphenate="OFF" TextAlign="Center"><change>PART XI</change></Para></Block><Block LineCnt="N" Align="Yes" KeepWith="Next"><!--Heading:READING MATERIAL--><Para TopMargin="5" Hyphenate="OFF" TextAlign="Center"><change>READING MATERIAL</change></Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2"><change><B>1.</B> A supply of any book, periodical literature or other reading material.</change></Para></Block><Block Align="Yes"><Para Style="BPT_ImprintE"><br/><br/>Published under authority of the Senate of Canada</Para></Block><Block Align="Yes" LineCnt="N"><Para NoLineBreak="Yes" NoHtml="Yes" Leading="0" Size="0" TopMargin="0" BottomMargin="0">Â</Para></Block></Bill_Part></Bill>
